<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="253" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognized among species of 
<taxonomicName box="[672,784,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[672,784,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Corixidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the uniformly dark coloration, macropterous forewing without a pale band (
<figureCitation box="[393,493,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-217@3.[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Corixidea graziae sp. nov., Corixidea quilombola sp. nov., and Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691704/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Figure 2</figureCitation>
), mediotergite 8 asymmetrical, with process insertion on the left side (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1423,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
), process of mediotergite 8 laterally directed, composed of an elongate thin projection with serrated distal portion composed of four small teeth (
<figureCitation box="[491,610,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
); right paramere elongate and narrowed, strongly arched, bearing a strong claw-like projection and a row of four fine setae on the tip (
<figureCitation box="[818,938,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
