<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2021" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2021" box="[585,705,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[585,705,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[715,808,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[715,808,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authority="Emsley, 1969" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[959,1234,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beebei">
<emphasis box="[959,1068,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. beebei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emsley, M. G." box="[1078,1234,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref4419" refString="Emsley, M. G. (1969) The Schizopteridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) with the descriptions of new species from Trinidad. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 25, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1969">Emsley, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Trinidad &amp; Tobago</collectingCountry>
a laterally directed process of mediotergite 8 but differs in having the distal portion of the process of mediotergite 8 bearing a row of four small teeth in the posterior surface. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[984,1089,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beebei">
<emphasis box="[984,1089,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. beebei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these teeth are lacking, and the anterior surface is ornamented with many tiny pointed projections distally, which are absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2021" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2021" box="[1222,1339,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1339,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Also, the right paramere of 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2021" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2021" box="[468,586,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[468,586,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[594,685,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[594,685,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is arched, bearing a strong claw-like projection and a row of four fine setae on the tip. The right paramere of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[631,736,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beebei">
<emphasis box="[631,736,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. beebei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost straight, without setae, and with a very small pointed projection apically. The new species seems to belong to the 
<emphasis box="[812,879,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">major</emphasis>
species group due to the laterally directed process on tergum 8 (
<bibRefCitation author="Knyshov, A. &amp; Hoey-Chamberlain, R. &amp; Weirauch, C." box="[301,534,439,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" pagination="985 - 995" refId="ref4752" refString="Knyshov, A., Hoey-Chamberlain, R. &amp; Weirauch, C. (2019) Hybrid enrichment of poorly preserved museum specimens refines homology hypotheses in a group of minute litter bugs (Hemiptera: Dipsocoromorpha: Schizopteridae). Systematic Entomology, 44 (4), 985 - 995. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12368" type="journal article" year="2019">
Knyshov 
<emphasis box="[410,467,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
